	<header class="single-header border mb-3">
	
		
	<h1 class="title" style="text-align: center">
		<b>Do Presidential Alerts Give the Government Total Access to Your Phone?</b></h1>
	
	
	
		<h2 class="subtitle">
			Software engineer and cryptocurrency advocate John McAfee claimed the presidential alert system gives the government access to your phone. We found no evidence to support that claim. 	</h2>
	
	
	
		<ul class="list-unstyled authors list-unstyled d-flex flex-wrap comma-separated">
	
			
								<li>
						<a class="font-weight-bold" href="">
							Author:Alex Kasprak					</a>
					</li>
				
			
		</ul>
	
	
	
		
	
	
	
	
	
		
		
			
			
	
			
		
	</header>
	
	
	
	
	
		
	
		<div class="card mb-3">
	
			<div class="card-header">
				<h3 class="h6" style="font-weight: 700">Claim</h3>
			</div>
	
			<div class="claim-text card-body">
	
				“Presidential alerts” are capable of accessing the E911 chip in your phones, which provides the government full access to your location, microphone, camera and every function of your phone.
			</div>
	
		</div>
		<br>
	
	
	
	
		<div class="card mb-3">
	
			<div class="card-header">
